(143, 5,N'Such a mess. Finished it just because I dont like to leave stuff halfway through. I can see all the money they had put into this game and the designers and 3d-modelers hard work, but it simply does not pay off. This is just a bunch of nice assets awkwardly put together. The fighting system works and seems interesting at the beginning but by the end, it is barely enjoyable, spamming skills and rolling around from hundreds of enemies to... what? To get a new pair of the same-looking rounded glasses (no no no we still do not get that this is a Harry-Potter-inspired game)? 33 copies of the same old black cloak? Same thing with exploring -- theres simply no reason to explore the giant territory of non-interesting copy-paste bandit and goblin camps, a stupid forest that spread across the Highlands that looks exactly the same at any point of your destination (apart from the small part to the south) to get a bunch of decorative pieces. To be honest, I could go on and brag about every aspect of it, from the upgrade system and the way you progress through it to the story (arghhhh), but this game does not deserve any kind of critique written toward it.',N'2024-06-07'),
